cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the performance of deep learning methods for predicting a chaotic system, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of these methods for modeling complex nonlinear dynamical systems also relates to systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the comparison of different deep learning methods, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of these methods to weather/climate modeling relates to computational engineering (cs.CE).
